-- China Plans to Meet United Nations Development Goals by 2015, Xinhua Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-21T16:22:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/china-plans-to-meet-united-nations-development-goals-by-2015-xinhua-says.html
China will be able to meet all of
its Millennium Development Goals by 2015, Xinhua said, citing
Renata Dessallien, the United Nations Development Program
Resident Representative in China.  China has already met its targets for reducing poverty and
hunger, enrolling children in school and reducing child and
infant mortality, Xinhua said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
